---
title: weave-riff Connection Flow
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant Host as Host (Fleet App)
    participant Server as Signaling Server
    participant Viewer as Viewer (Fleet App)
    participant TURN as STUN/TURN

    Note over Host,Viewer: Phase 1: Share Registration
    Host->>Server: POST /api/sessions/share (API Key)
    Server-->>Host: { token, uri: "weave-riff://join/abc123" }

    Note over Host,Viewer: Phase 2: Viewer Joins
    Host-->>Viewer: Sends link (Slack, email, etc.)
    Viewer->>Server: GET /join/abc123 (OIDC auth)
    Server-->>Viewer: Redirect → weave-riff://join/abc123

    Note over Host,Viewer: Phase 3: WebRTC Signaling
    Viewer->>Server: WS: SDP Offer
    Server->>Host: WS: SDP Offer (forwarded)
    Host->>Server: WS: SDP Answer
    Server->>Viewer: WS: SDP Answer (forwarded)

    loop ICE Candidate Exchange
        Viewer->>Server: WS: ICE Candidate
        Server->>Host: WS: ICE Candidate
        Host->>Server: WS: ICE Candidate
        Server->>Viewer: WS: ICE Candidate
    end

    Host-.->TURN: STUN binding request
    Viewer-.->TURN: STUN binding request

    Note over Host,Viewer: Phase 4: Direct P2P (Server steps aside)
    Host->>Viewer: catch-up snapshot (messages + meta)
    Viewer->>Host: identity (displayName)

    loop Session Streaming
        Host->>Viewer: event (agent output, tokens, files)
    end

    Viewer->>Host: suggest (prompt text)
    Host->>Viewer: suggestion-response (accept/reject)
    Host->>Viewer: event (accepted prompt executes)
